2026-04-05 | Generate Gray Code Sequence

	Question
Return all numbers representing Gray code of n bits.

	Approach
Direct formula for Gray code:
		Gray(i) = i ^ (i >> 1)

Steps:
1.	Iterate i from 0 to (2ⁿ - 1)  
2.	Compute:
		i ^ (i >> 1)  
3.	Add to result  

	Time Complexity
	O(2ⁿ)

	Space Complexity
	O(2ⁿ)

	Solution

class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> grayCode(int n) {

        vector<int> ans;

        int size = 1 << n;

        for(int i = 0; i < size; i++){
            ans.push_back(i ^ (i >> 1));
        }

        return ans;
    }
};

	Key Insight
The formula:
		i ^ (i >> 1)

ensures:
- consecutive values differ by exactly one bit  
- sequence starts from 0  

This is the most optimal and elegant way to generate Gray code.
